  "update_count": 46,
  "description_snippet": "**VULNERABILITY DETAILS**   \nIn WebRTC pcm16b codecs audio decoder, there is no check in WebRtcPcm16b_Decode for ensuring `encoded length` less or equal than `speech` buffer size. This makes assigning speech[i] possible to trigger a buffer overflow when decoding a frame which `len` > `speech` buffer"
